Hydrogen fluoride, a highly corrosive inorganic acid, also known as hydrofluoric acid. It is used in the production of refrigerants, herbicides, pharmaceuticals, and for etching glass.
Hydrogen cyanide, a highly poisonous and volatile inorganic acid, also known as hydrocyanic acid. It is used in chemical synthesis, fumigation, and mining for gold extraction.
Hydrogen bromide, a strong inorganic acid also known as hydrobromic acid. It is used to produce bromide compounds and as a catalyst in chemical reactions.
Arsenic acid, a toxic inorganic acid. It is primarily used for treating wood to prevent rot, as a finishing agent for glass, and in the synthesis of some dyes and organic arsenic compounds.
High-purity Sulphamidic acid (also known as Sulfamic acid), a chemical compound that may contain a small amount of an anti-caking agent like silicon dioxide.

Phosphorous acid, also known as Phosphonic acid, available in solid or liquid (water-based) forms. It is a chemical compound used in various industrial applications, including as a reducing agent or in the production of phosphite salts.
